libtwin
------------------------------------------
With embedded systems gaining high resolution displays and powerful
cpus, the desire for sophisticated graphical user interfaces can be
realized in even the smallest of systems. While the cpupower available
for a given power budget has increased dramatically, these tiny
systems remain severely memory constrained. This unique environment
presents interesting challenges in graphical system design and
implementation. To explore this particular space, a new window system,
Twin, has been developed. Using ideas from modern window systems in
larger environments, Twin offers overlapping translucent windows,
anti-aliased graphics and scalable fonts in a total memory budget of
100KB.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.0.2-1
  cygwin-devel-2.0.2-1
  libfreetype6-2.5.5-1
  libjpeg-devel-1.3.1-3
  libjpeg8-1.3.1-3
  libpng16-1.6.17-1
  libpng16-devel-1.6.17-1
  libtwin-devel-0.0.3-1bl5
  libtwin0-0.0.3-1bl5
  libX11-devel-1.6.3-1
  libX11_6-1.6.3-1
  libXau-devel-1.0.8-1
  libxcb-devel-1.10-1
  libXdmcp-devel-1.1.2-1
  zlib-devel-1.2.8-3
  zlib0-1.2.8-3

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-13-1
  automake-9-1
  binutils-2.25-1
  cygport-0.18.1-1
  gcc-core-4.9.2-3
  libtool-2.4.6-1
  make-4.1-1

Canonical website:
  http://ozlabs.org/~jk/projects/petitboot/

Canonical download:
  http://ozlabs.org/~jk/projects/petitboot/downloads/libtwin-0.0.3.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libtwin-0.0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libtwin-0.0.3-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libtwin-0.0.3-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtwin-0.0.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtwin0-0.0.3-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libtwin-devel-0.0.3-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libtwin)
  /usr/bin/twin_ttf.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libtwin.README
  /usr/share/doc/libtwin/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libtwin/ChangeLog

(libtwin0)
  /usr/bin/cygtwin-0.dll

(libtwin-devel)
  /usr/include/libtwin/twin.h
  /usr/include/libtwin/twin_jpeg.h
  /usr/include/libtwin/twin_linux_mouse.h
  /usr/include/libtwin/twin_png.h
  /usr/include/libtwin/twin_x11.h
  /usr/lib/libtwin.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libtwin.pc

